<p>In your terminal, move to the place where you build websites and type:</p>
<pre><code class="lang-bash">$ git clone git@github.com:growdigital/groundwork.git
</code></pre>
<p>This clones the Groundwork git repository onto your computer. Then, change directory into groundwork:</p>
<pre><code class="lang-bash">$ cd groundwork
</code></pre>
<p>Cool. To complete the installation, you need to install the myriad Node.js plugins for the website to work:</p>
<pre><code class="lang-bash">$ npm install
</code></pre>
<p>Should take just a few minutes. When that’s finished, you can start up the development server!</p>
<pre><code class="lang-bash">$ npm run dev
</code></pre>
<p>Way to go! This <em>should</em> start up a web browser and display the blank Groundwork website, looking a little like this:</p>
<p><img src="/assets/images/01setup.png" alt="Screenshot of blank Groundwork website working on local dev server"></p>
